modules.description: Wraps ZeroMQ sockets for asynchronous message passing, providing non-blocking receive and send operations for single and multi-part messages. Operates on ZeroMQ socket objects and their typed wrappers, enabling integration with Async and Lwt frameworks. Supports extracting raw sockets for low-level manipulation and ensures safe closure of resources.

Provides asynchronous message passing between processes using ZeroMQ sockets, supporting publish-subscribe, request-reply, and push-pull patterns. Operates on socket descriptors, message buffers, and event loops implemented with Lwt. Enables real-time data streaming and distributed task coordination in networked applications.

Provides asynchronous message passing through ZeroMQ sockets, supporting non-blocking send and receive operations for single and multi-part messages. Handles typed socket wrappers and raw socket extraction, enabling integration with Async and Lwt. Allows safe resource management and low-level socket manipulation. Examples include streaming data between processes, handling message queues, and building distributed systems with non-blocking I/O.
